  "gloss": "For the transport class of readouts, the transport-discrepancy quantity does not factor through the bisimulation partition: no function recovers it from the partition alone. A concrete pair of dynamics induces the same partition yet differs in transport discrepancy, so the partition does not determine the readout.\n\n**Cites** `WMSpec.RigidityDichotomy.kernelFiber_not_factorsThrough` — the corpus theorem this result restates and discharges.\n\n**Original contribution.** The raw lemma is a non-factorization fact about specific objects; the thesis-layer statement pairs it against the rigid half as the second, closure-poor pole of a genuine dichotomy.\n",
